
conlluf-conllus.awk

  Transform the `false` conllu files to the `.conllus` files.

long-short.awk

  Transform the A[0-9M] to ARG[0-9M] arguments.

short-long.awk

  Inverse of the previous script.

args.awk

  Used for extracting all occurrences of predicate arguments. Useful
  in conjunction with sort and uniq.

  % awk -f ../scripts/args.awk *.conllus | sort | uniq -c
18749 ARG0
34238 ARG1
   27 ARG1-DSP
12170 ARG2
  807 ARG3
  509 ARG4
    6 ARG5

test-conllus.awk

  In the `.conllus` files, the number of columns inside a sentence is
  fixed. The script can be used to check it.

  awk -f ../scripts/test-conllus.awk *.conllus | grep -v "#" | sort | uniq -c

  It must produce no lines with different pair of numbers.
